modules.description: Provides syntax extensions for defining anonymous functions with named parameters, using [%f ...] and [%f_ ...] to simplify function literals. Operates on OCaml's abstract syntax tree to rewrite function expressions with unique parameter names. Useful for creating concise, readable function literals in code that requires frequent use of anonymous functions.

Parses strings into placeholder structures, manages list additions, and performs downward folding over integers. It processes and transforms expressions by replacing placeholders while tracking context. It includes rules and extensions for syntax expansion and manipulation within a ppx framework.
